l. Near the surface of Earth,\nclock comparisons at the $1 \\times 10^{-18}$ level provide 1 cm resolution\nalong gravity, outperforming state-of-the-art geodetic techniques. These\noptical clocks can further be used to explore geophysical phenomena, detect\ngravitational waves, test general relativity and search for dark matter.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 30 Jul 2018 10:56:38 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-12-13"}
